{"id":14881512,"mediaExerciseId":"8f4bd1f9-c91c-4b0b-ab08-648d3f9aad46","exerciseName":"10","chapterName":"15","chapterTitle":"Raising Capital","groupId":612403,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":530,"solutions":[{"id":6025231,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we are asked to assess the IPO pricing. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":28,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/40b9ad3554def9356b6f32378116d000/52ec54027eb3417f7aa0a60cd102ee37/lateximg_large.png","width":733},"regular":{"height":15,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/40b9ad3554def9356b6f32378116d000/52ec54027eb3417f7aa0a60cd102ee37/lateximg.png","width":366}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"The procedure of issuing shares of a private company to the market in the issuance of new stock is known as an **initial public offering (IPO)**. This enables a company to generate revenue from the general public.\n\n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":103,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/40b9ad3554def9356b6f32378116d000/caba57c3d3ed19201a24ac6e95d4555b/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/40b9ad3554def9356b6f32378116d000/caba57c3d3ed19201a24ac6e95d4555b/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"## A. \n\nThe first public offering is often underpriced, as shown by the prospectus presented. However, this is not a problem for the firm since investment firms expect share prices to rise to a level that investors consider valuable, such as this small offering. Investors may be willing to take a chance on a new offering after being appraised.\n\nIf the listing price is high or low, the issuing firm may incur costs. If the issue is priced high, it can be assumed that the offering of securities will be unsuccessful and have to be removed; yet, if the offer is priced below the true market value, it may be successful.\n\n**As a result, the firm should underprice its offering price.**","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"## B. \n\n\nSince the stockbroker is notifying an investor that the firm is coming public and selling several hundred shares at the offering price, the stockbroker may be having difficulty selling the securities. **As a result, this offering will not be underpriced.** \n\nRegardless of whether the offering was underpriced or not, the firm becomes a publicly-traded company controlled by its investors when it hits the market. In the future, the stock's market price will be determined by investor interest.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"a92aa291-75b9-4c55-af4b-d67995fe1978","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":4}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881513,"exerciseName":"1","page":531,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"9145c521-c0cd-4a17-8cd0-a365dfbb57bc","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-15-critical-thinking-questions-1-9145c521-c0cd-4a17-8cd0-a365dfbb57bc"},{"id":14881514,"exerciseName":"2","page":531,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"1d20aec4-00ce-4a30-9464-13cd2a5d107a","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-15-critical-thinking-questions-2-1d20aec4-00ce-4a30-9464-13cd2a5d107a"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881511,"exerciseName":"9","page":529,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"f138bb53-cb83-44e3-8503-aafb796e590d","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-15-critical-thinking-questions-9-f138bb53-cb83-44e3-8503-aafb796e590d"},{"id":14881510,"exerciseName":"8","page":529,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"6d832f9c-2524-48be-99c0-15c940bc7224","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-15-critical-thinking-questions-8-6d832f9c-2524-48be-99c0-15c940bc7224"}],"_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-15-critical-thinking-questions-10-8f4bd1f9-c91c-4b0b-ab08-648d3f9aad46"}